<HEAD>Wet and Wild Weather Forecast For Much of Nation</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: LEADS with 4 grafs to UPDATE with new storms, hail and flooding,
one death reported; PICKS UP 3rd graf, `Six people ...'; DELETES outdated
8th graf pvs, `Severe thunderstorm ...'</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Warm, humid air streaming north from the Gulf of Mexico clashed
with high-altitude winds today, creating violent thunderstorms in
Oklahoma and Texas.
   A pregnant mother of five died when winds overturned her mobile
home Tuesday night near Garden City, in western Texas, authorities
said. The woman's oldest child suffered a broken leg.
   The storms moved through northern Texas early today, causing hail
the size of golf balls and flash flooding that stranded motorists
and apartment dwellers in Wichita Falls.
   Flash-flood war, and much of the central and southern Plains, and
severe thunderstorms across north central and northeast Texas and
much of Oklahoma.
   High temperatures were forecast in the upper 60s over northeast
Minnesota, and along portions of the California coast; in the 90s
from southern and central Texas across the southern Rockies, the
southern Plateau and inland valleys of California into southern
Oregon, as well as over southern Minnesota; above 100 degrees over
the desert Southwest and the Rio Grande Valley of Texas, and in the
70s and 80s over much of the rest of the nation.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 39
degrees at Yellowstone National Park, Wyo., to 85 degrees at Blythe,
Calif.
   Other reports:
   _ East: Atlanta 65 fair; Boston 56 cloudy; Buffalo 57 partly
cloudy; Charleston, S.C., 70 partly cloudy; Cincinnati 55 fair;
Cleveland 59 partly cloudy; Detroit 61 fair; Miami 73 rain; New York
63 rain; Philadelphia 66 rain; Pittsburgh 63 cloudy; Portland,
Maine, 56 cloudy; Washington 66 rain.
   _ Central: Bismarck 62 fair; Chicago 67 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth
74 partly cloudy; Denver 54 partly cloudy; Des Moines 62 fair;
Indianapolis 61 fair; Kansas City 64 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 72
fair; Nashville 58 fair; St. Louis 67 fair.
   _ West: Anchorage 53 partly cloudy; Las Vegas 79 fair; Los
Angeles 59 fair; Phoenix 80 fair; Salt Lake City 57 fair; San Diego
64 cloudy; San Francisco 55 cloudy; Seattle 53 fair.
   _ Canada: Montreal 59 partly cloudy; Toronto 59 rain.
