<HEAD>Man Caught Mud-Handed With 27 Rolls of Stolen Sod</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police say they caught a modern-day ``sodbuster''
mud-handed with 27 rolls of stolen sod in the front and back seats
of his car.
   Donald Spearman, 39, was arrested Tuesday and charged with
stealing newly laid turf from a parkway, police said.
   Spearman, who had been doing landscaping in a Chicago suburb,
told police he had bought the sod, said Capt. Richard Wedgbury. But
a witness reported seeing him remove the turf early Tuesday, police
said.
   Moreover, police said they made Spearman put the sod back and it
fit perfectly into the blank spots along the parkway.
   Officers said they knew they had their man because he was covered
with mud.
