<HEAD>Israeli Gunship Attacks Hezbollah Guerrillas</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SIDON, Lebanon (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An Israeli helicopter gunship attacked
pro-Iranian guerrillas in south Lebanon after they launched a rocket
into Israel's border ``security zone'' Wednesday, police reported.
   A police spokesman said the gunship fired ``three rockets at
Hezbollah positions'' southeast of Jbaa at midday and at least three
guerrillas were wounded.
   He said the attack near the mountain town occurred after
Hezbollah militiamen fired the rocket into Marjayoun in the Israeli
zone, which ranges in depth from six to 10 miles just north of the
border.
   The rocket ``exploded in a residential area of Marjayoun at 10:10
a.m.'' but no casualty reort was available, the spokesman said.
   About the air attack, the spokesman said: ``Dust and smoke
billowed from the stricken positions'' on a wooded slope on the
western flank of the Israeli zone. ``Hezbollahis fired anti-aircraft
guns at the gunship, but it was not hit.''
   It was the sixth Israeli air raid in Lebanon this year. On May
31, Israeli jets raided Palestinian and Hezbollah bases in south and
east Lebanon, killing two people and wounding 12.
