<FIRST>r i AM-Uganda     06-07 0136</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Uganda,0141</SECOND>
<HEAD>Rebels Kill 100 People in Northern Uganda</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KAMPALA, Uganda (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rebel ambushes killed at least 100 people
in northern Uganda in the past week, a government official said
Wednesday.
   Charles Alai, deputy minister of commerce, said the ambushes were
staged in Gulu Province by Holy Spirit Movement guerrillas.
   ``Some people were killed in attacks on convoys, while others _
especially displaced people who normally frequent the rural areas
from the towns hunting for food _ also fell victim,'' Alai said in
an interview.
   The Holy Spirit Movement was thought to have been crushed in 1987
when its former leader, warrior-priestess Alice Lakena, fled to
neighboring Kenya, where she has been detained.
   Remnants of her movement regrouped in northern Uganda last year,
however, and have evaded army sweeps aimed at stamping them out.
</TEXT>
