<FIRST>r f AM-Hershey     06-07 0123</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Hershey,0129</SECOND>
<HEAD>Hershey To Build New Chocolate Factory</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HERSHEY, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Hershey Foods Corp. announced Wednesday it
will build a $100 million chocolate factory near its existing plant
here.
   Groundbreaking is set for late this summer for the plant, which
will be about 130,000 square feet and process chocolate for the
company's main factory.
   The new factory will have about 60 new employees. But start-up
will mean a reduction of employees at the main factory as new
machinery replaces older, less-efficient equipment, the company said.
   Hershey Foods President Kenneth Wolfe said it was not yet known
how many employees at the main plant will be affected. But he said
the company will try to ease job reductions through retraining and
attrition.
</TEXT>
