<FIRST>u f AM-American-Maintenance     06-07 0306</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-American-Maintenance,0316</SECOND>
<HEAD>American to Build New Maintenance Facility, Expand Another</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   American Airlines continued its
expansion Wednesday, announcing it would spend up to $550 million to
build one maintenance facility and expand another to service the
airline's growing fleet.
   American Chairman Robert L. Crandall said the carrier will build
a $400 million maintenance and service facility at Fort Worth
Alliance Airport, ending a hard-fought battle between Texas and
Oklahoma that had involved the governors of both states.
   Crandall also announced a $150 million expansion of the airline's
current maintenance facility in Tulsa, Okla.
   Alliance Airport is 12 miles northwest of Dallas-Fort Worth
International Airport, where American is based and operates its
largest hub. American is the nation's biggest airline.
   The Alliance maintenance center will be built on 207 acres and
include a series of hangars, shops and support buildings. Initial
construction will start next January and cost about $222 million.
The first phase should be completed by the end of 1991, the airline
said.
   Initial employment will be about 2,500 people, but could exceed
4,500 by completion.
   Crandall said American will spend $150 million to add a hangar at
Tulsa, which will increase employment there by 1,600 people. The
Tulsa facility, already undergoing a $250 million expansion,
currently employs some 6,100 people.
   The larger maintenance operation has become necessary to service
American's expanding fleet, which will grow from about 480 jets
currently to about 752 by the mid-1990s. The carrier recently
announced several multi-billion-dollar contracts for new jets for
both its main operation and its commuter airline subsidiary,
American Eagle.
   AMR Corp., American's parent, recently announced record
first-quarter earnings of $101 million. AMR plans a $95 million
expansion of its headquarters building in Fort Worth and is working
on plans to build a $1 billion terminal at Dallas-Fort Worth
International Airport.
</TEXT>
